{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id7a533b36-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s6105"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"6105"},"text":"§ 6105.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Administration and applicability of chapter","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id7a533b37-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s6105/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" In general","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Except as otherwise provided in sections 6102(d), 6102(e), 6103, and 6104 of this title, this chapter shall be enforced by the Commission under the Federal Trade Commission Act (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s41"},"text":"15 U.S.C. 41","children":[],"tail":" et seq.). Consequently, no activity which is outside the jurisdiction of that Act shall be affected by this chapter."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id7a533b38-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s6105/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Actions by Commission","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Commission shall prevent any person from violating a rule of the Commission under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s6102"},"text":"section 6102 of this title","children":[],"tail":" in the same manner, by the same means, and with the same jurisdiction, powers, and duties as though all applicable terms and provisions of the Federal Trade Commission Act ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s41"},"text":"15 U.S.C. 41","children":[],"tail":" et seq.) were incorporated into and made a part of this chapter. Any person who violates such rule shall be subject to the penalties and entitled to the privileges and immunities provided in the Federal Trade Commission Act in the same manner, by the same means, and with the same jurisdiction, power, and duties as though all applicable terms and provisions of the Federal Trade Commission Act were incorporated into and made a part of this chapter."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id7a533b39-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s6105/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Effect on other laws","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Nothing contained in this chapter shall be construed to limit the authority of the Commission under any other provision of law.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id7a533b3a-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s6105/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Enforcement by Bureau of Consumer Financial Protection","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Except as otherwise provided in sections 6102(d), 6102(e), 6103, and 6104 of this title, and subject to subtitle B of the Consumer Financial Protection Act of 2010 [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s5511"},"text":"12 U.S.C. 5511","children":[],"tail":" et seq.], this chapter shall be enforced by the Bureau of Consumer Financial Protection under subtitle E of the Consumer Financial Protection Act of 2010 ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s5561"},"text":"12 U.S.C. 5561","children":[],"tail":" et seq.], with respect to the offering or provision of a consumer financial product or service subject to that Act."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id7a533b3b-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/297/s6"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–297, § 6","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-08-16"},"text":"Aug. 16, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/1549"},"text":"108 Stat. 1549","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/203/tX/s1100C/d"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–203, title X, § 1100C(d)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2010-07-21"},"text":"July 21, 2010","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/124/2111"},"text":"124 Stat. 2111","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id7a533b3c-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id7a533b3d-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id7a533b3e-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Federal Trade Commission Act, referred to in subsecs. (a) and (b), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1914-09-26/ch311"},"text":"act Sept. 26, 1914, ch. 311","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/38/717"},"text":"38 Stat. 717","children":[],"tail":", which is classified generally to subchapter I (§ 41 et seq.) of chapter 2 of this title. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s58"},"text":"section 58 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This chapter, referred to in subsecs. (c) and (d), was in the original “this Act”, meaning ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/297"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–297","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-08-16"},"text":"Aug. 16, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/1545"},"text":"108 Stat. 1545","children":[],"tail":", which is classified principally to this chapter. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s6101"},"text":"section 6101 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Consumer Financial Protection Act of 2010, referred to in subsec. (d), is title X of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/203"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–203","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2010-07-21"},"text":"July 21, 2010","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/124/1955"},"text":"124 Stat. 1955","children":[],"tail":". Subtitles B (§§ 1021–1029A) and E (§§ 1051–1058) of the Act are classified generally to parts B (§ 5511 et seq.) and E (§ 5561 et seq.), respectively, of subchapter V of chapter 53 of Title 12, Banks and Banking. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id7a533b3f-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2010—Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/203"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–203","children":[],"tail":" added subsec. (d)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id7a533b40-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id7a533b41-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2010 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/203"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–203","children":[],"tail":" effective on the designated transfer date, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/203/s1100H"},"text":"section 1100H of Pub. L. 111–203","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s552a"},"text":"section 552a of Title 5","children":[],"tail":", Government Organization and Employees."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
